lusions that are essential for understanding the class and gender characteristics of social criticism and activism in this period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356516640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773565166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773565166/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles